"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">7</A>
Seriphos, an island of the Cyclades group, a symbol of smallness and insignificance.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note8" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Cato_Maior_de_Senectute/text*.html#ref8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">8</A>
This law was proposed by M. Cincius Alimentus in 204 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> and prohibited lawyers from receiving fees from clients and the rich from receiving gifts from the poor for services. Cato's irrelevant digression here is a happy illustration of Cicero's art in impressing us with Cato's age.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note9" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Cato_Maior_de_Senectute/text*.html#ref9
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">9</A>
Cicero blunders here, for it was M. Livius Macatus, a relation of Salinator, who held the citadel,
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/livy/liv.27.shtml#34
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,190)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Livy <SPAN CLASS="small">XXVII</SPAN>.34.7</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note10" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Cato_Maior_de_Senectute/text*.html#ref10
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">10</A>
Gaius Flaminius was popular tribune in 232 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> when this law was enacted. It provided for the settlement of citizen farmers on public lands, and resembled somewhat the American homestead laws. Cicero gives the date here as in the second <SPAN CLASS="whole">consul</SPAN>&shy;ship of Q. Fabius Maximus, <I>i.e.</I> 228 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
