"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">12</A>
Laelius and Scipio, at the death of Ennius, were respectively seventeen and sixteen years old.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note13" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Cato_Maior_de_Senectute/text*.html#ref13
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">13</A>
This law, named from its author, Voconius Saxa, tribune of the plebs, passed in 169 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, provided (1) that no one enrolled as having 100,000 <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">asses</SPAN> (about $1,000) should make a woman his heir; or (2) leave to another a sum greater than the heirs would receive.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


