Referring to the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">arbiter bibendi</SPAN>, or <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">rex</SPAN> — also called <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">magister</SPAN> — <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">convivi</SPAN>. The word "toast-masters" as used in the United States is the exact equivalent of the Latin. They were appointed with due ceremony even at public banquets.


